#!/bin/bash
# Open magit status for a directory from caja "Open With"
exec emacsclient -c -a "" -e "(magit-status \"$1\")"

# ============================================================================
# I used to use [TortoiseHg][tortoisehg] to browse version control status on
# my linux workstation.  I wanted to do likewise with git in my Ubuntu
# [MATE][mate] desktop.  The file browser is called caja.
# [TortoiseGit][tortoisegit] doesn't support linux.
#
# ## Overlay icons
#
# [git-nautilus-icons][git-nautilus-icons] -- git status emblems on files in
# caja:
#
#     sudo apt install python3-caja python3-pip
#     pip3 install --user git-nautilus-icons
#     killall caja
#
# Supply chain: 56 stars, 5 forks, 79 commits, 1 maintainer.  Latest [PyPI
# release][pypi] 2.2.0 (Oct 2025).  BSD-2-Clause.
#
# ## Full context menu
#
# [RabbitVCS][rabbitvcs] (most like TortoiseHg) -- commit, push, pull, log,
# diff from right-click.  Has a [Caja client][rabbitvcs-caja] in source, but
# no apt package -- must install from source.
#
# Supply chain: 396 stars, 117 forks, 1952 commits, broader contributor
# base.  Latest release v0.19 (Jul 2023).  GPL-2.0.
#
# ## Workflow: caja to magit
#
# My current habit is [magit][magit], but getting there from caja was a
# bunch of manual steps.  Here is what I settled on.
#
# ### The working setup
#
# This wrapper script at `dotfiles/bin/magit-status`, plus a [desktop
# entry][desktop-entry-spec] at `dotfiles/applications/emacs-magit.desktop`:
#
#     [Desktop Entry]
#     Name=Magit status
#     Comment=Open magit status for this directory
#     Exec=magit-status %F
#     Icon=emacs
#     Type=Application
#     StartupNotify=false
#     MimeType=inode/directory;
#
# Symlinked into place by `dotfiles/Makefile`:
#
#     TARGETS += $(HOME)/.local/share/applications/emacs-magit.desktop
#     TARGETS += $(HOME)/.local/bin/magit-status
#
# Run `make` in `dotfiles/`, then right-click any directory in caja ->
# Open With -> Magit status.
#
# ### Pitfalls encountered
#
# **Caja-actions don't work for directories.**  Caja has an Actions submenu
# in the right-click context menu, but it only appears for files with
# specific MIME types, not for inode/directory.  Creating a Type=Action
# desktop entry with MimeTypes=inode/directory; produces no visible menu
# item.
#
# **NoDisplay=true hangs caja.**  Setting NoDisplay=true in a desktop entry
# with MimeType=inode/directory; causes caja to hang when browsing any
# directory containing the desktop file.  Omitting NoDisplay=true fixes this.
#
# **emacsclient without -a "" hangs.**  If no Emacs server is running,
# emacsclient -c blocks indefinitely.  The -a "" flag makes emacsclient
# start Emacs as a daemon if no server is found.
#
# **Use a wrapper script, not inline bash in Exec.**  The desktop file Exec
# key does not handle complex quoting well.  Early attempts with
# bash -c '...' and %% date-format escapes were brittle -- the %% escaping
# was silently dropped by caja.  A standalone script in PATH avoids all
# quoting problems.
#
# **Use %F, not %f.**  Caja's "Open With" passes the target path via field
# codes in the Exec line.  %F (capital F, passes all selected files) is what
# VS Codium's desktop entry uses and is more robust than %f (single file).
#
# [tortoisehg]: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TortoiseHg
# [mate]: https://mate-desktop.org/
# [tortoisegit]: https://tortoisegit.org/
# [git-nautilus-icons]: https://github.com/chrisjbillington/git-nautilus-icons
# [pypi]: https://pypi.org/project/git-nautilus-icons/
# [rabbitvcs]: https://github.com/rabbitvcs/rabbitvcs
# [rabbitvcs-caja]: https://github.com/rabbitvcs/rabbitvcs/tree/master/clients/caja
# [magit]: https://magit.vc/
# [desktop-entry-spec]: https://specifications.freedesktop.org/desktop-entry-spec/latest/
# ============================================================================
